column5: Have a crew member wavering with family illness isues. Will know by 11pm if they are in or out for sure... but at this time of year 3 guys in the boat is a safer crew out there. If you are interested in going Muskie Fishing.. 8:50 AM tomorrow (tuesday).. and you can be in Midland for launch time.. please send me a PM so I know that you are interested and will contact you by 11PM to say yah.. or na. to the  position being available.  If need be, I can supply the appropriate muskie gear if you are handicapped in that regard.  -5C to start the day.. high of Zero and sunny with cloudy periods (we hope)...will be out for about 8 hours.. dress for ice fishing ;o)  Wayne
damn  damn, work is  always getting in the way of my life
gosh darn no car to get to midland... do I hitch hike now....
Man... I guess you all have to go to work??  Honest.. I had a shower yesterday !  Life's too short fellas... live it while you can...
Can you give me a note so i can take the day off work ? lol I was out in the boat yesterday 4.5 inches of snow while i was fishing whites on my lake.

Dear Rent-all Boss,  Mr. Daume was seen in my boat today and appears to have a severe case of anal glaucoma.  He will be absent from work on Tuesday December 8th for extensive testing of his desires to continue in his current occupation.  Dr. M. Lunge
Now that is funny!  If I didn't have a hole to fill myself Wayne!...
Dr. isn't good at spelling though! lol  You can get here by 9 Ron !!!
Awww rats!  I would LOVE to fish with Dr. Lunge!!!!  Obviously you're prolly out there by now, Wayne...good luck!
DANG !!!!  I wish I would'a checked the board last night !!!  I would have made the trek this morning !!  Maybe next time.  Meely

Didn't miss much lads... other than a BEAUTIFUL day on the water!! We didn't get much of that sun they promised. Boat's covered in ice head to toe.. thanks to the spray from 5 footers when coming back in. No issues launching or retrieving thanks to the ramp prep yesterday.  Sad.. but I think we may be done for the year. Some ice in the back bays... surface was 36 at the ramp... 42 out on the lake.
good to hear you're back safely. Any other boats out there today?
Nobody fishing... a couple of contractors out and about.
Glad to hear your back in Wayne.  Too bad I couldn't get up there. I have driven by your place in a roundabout way numerous times. I spent way to many weekends up North this year!
Like I said.. a Beautiful day on the water.  Glen.. didn't you see that rock on  your side....

Well bud its only a short time and we are running and gunning on the hard water once again. Lets see if we can top last years trip with over 300 km of lake running lol That boats looks good with the ice just needed some rum to go with it lol

I gave the note to my boss and he said that he was sorry but my work-I-tess was worse then the case of anal glaucoma. he made me  stay and work lol Thanks for the try Dr. M. Lunge but Dr Pay won in the end
